case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Partial skeletal parts only
case_address_found_2: Southeast shoreline of Big Break Beach
case_circumstances:
On 01-31-2012, a local citizen found two bones along the southeast shoreline of Big Break beach.  The citizen took the bones to the Contra Costa County Sheriff's Office Marie Patrol Division.  The bones were later examined by a Forensic Anthropologist, who determined one bone to be a human left tibia.  The second bone was only a fragment and not to be of human origin.
It is unknown how long the left tibia was lying on the shoreline.  No further evidence or means of identification for the tibia is available at this time.
